last_episode_to_air.name: Grand Finale
last_episode_to_air.overview: For the grand finale, the three remaining queens take on a memorable all-singing and all-dancing challenge before the final verdict.

name: Drag Race Belgique
overview: For the first time in its herstory, Belgium is welcoming the most glamorous drag competition. Hosted by the great French-Canadian diva, Rita Baga, Drag Race Belgique will demonstrate the immense talent and creativity of its drag scene. So be prepared for their audacity and authenticity!

episodes.name: Bonjour Everyone
episodes.overview: Ten Belgian queens will demonstrate all their creativity in a legendary talent show.

episodes.name: The Unavoidable
episodes.overview: This week, the queens will have to deploy all their business skills to promote an iconic Belgian food in a TV commercial.

episodes.name: Festival Realness
episodes.overview: They have a great sense of fashion but are they ready to use their beautifully manicured hands to sew the most flamboyant outfits? That’s what the queens will have to prove during a dreaded design challenge.

episodes.name: L’émission qui vous déshabille
episodes.overview: As the search for the first Belgian superstar drag continues, the queens will show all their acting skills in a parody of the much acclaimed “Ni juge, ni soumise” Belgian documentary.

episodes.name: Snatch Game
episodes.overview: This week, the queens take on the iconic Snatch Game challenge where they will have to deliver their best celebrity impersonations.

episodes.name: A deux c’est mieu!
episodes.overview: In this episode, the five remaining queens perform a complete drag makeover and transform five Belgian television personalities.

guest_stars.character: Self - Special Guest / Drag Jacky Van Piperzeel
guest_stars.name: Stéphane Piedboeuf

episodes.name: Discour de reine
episodes.overview: To prove they have the merits and skills to be crowned, our queens will deliver their first speech to the Belgian nation.

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: For the grand finale, the three queens will take on a memorable singing and dancing challenge before the final verdict.

episodes.name: De retour!
episodes.overview: In this premiere episode, the queens enter the werkroom for the first time and quickly take on their first challenge: a photoshoot on a rodeo unicorn. After this bumping ride, they will present a very personal and special act during a legendary Talent Show.

episodes.name: Drag-en-Ciel
episodes.overview: This week, our queens will have to demonstrate all their agility and glamour in a martial arts-themed photoshoot before taking on the very much feared Design Challenge.

episodes.name: Jawadde Dadde
episodes.overview: The temperature is going to rise as the queens form girl bands and perform in the fashion of the 90's.

episodes.name: Masquerade
episodes.overview: Nothing beats a Cha Cha Cha dance challenge, so this week, our queens are gonna shake their booties. And to add a bit of depth to those dancing legs, our queens will form the first Belgian Drag Government and present new laws to make Belgium great(er) again!

episodes.name: Snatch Game
episodes.overview: This week, there are two legendary challenges! The queens start by making fun of each other with puppets because... Everybody Loves Puppets! And then they will dive into the iconic Snatch Game!

episodes.name: Le Crime du Drag Express
episodes.overview: Tick tock! Tick tock! It’s time for drama! This week, the queens take on the reading challenge before embarking on a mysterious train. For their maxi challenge, the queens perform a parody of Agatha Christie's iconic “Murder on the Orient Express.”

episodes.name: Paquets cadeaux
episodes.overview: To make their way to the grand finale, our queens welcome a relative into the werkroom for a very emotional makeover challenge

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: For the grand finale, the three remaining queens take on a memorable all-singing and all-dancing challenge before the final verdict.
